items.summary: Lots of people like this place

items.text: Pancakes that are worth the five-hour wait on a Saturday, but if you go during the week you just might beat the crowd...
I don't care if you get the beloved blueberry pancakes or not, but the must have here is the SUGAR-CURED BACON!
Go to Clinton Street Baking Co. for dinner and order the blueberry pancakes. No line!
The tip list on foursquare is longer than the wait. You might finish reading by the time a table opens up!
Fucking sugar cured bacon. Fuck.
It's Pancake Month so there's a different specialty pancake every few days (from 8am-4pm and 6-11pm), including one with raspberries and raspberry-caramel sauce tomorrow. Only available on weekdays.
Avoid two-hour brunch lines by ordering the stack of blueberry pancakes for dinner.
Maple butter that comes with french toast & pancakes will make you feel feelings.
You'll likely have to wait a while to get a seat here around brunch time so when you do sit down, don't leave without getting their unbelievable blueberry pancakes and sugar cured bacon!
Try the Blueberry Pancakes
don't leave without tryig the sugar cured bacon!
Could this be the best brunch in NYC?  Expect a long, but worth it, wait.  Then devour an order of the Pear Waffles – a seasonal special!
Come by yo damn self to be seated with ease at the bar and be served in 5 minutes flat. Leave all friends and cohorts at their respective homes or cubicles.
Sweet mother of Baby Jesus, the fried chicken & waffles is everything it's cracked up to be. Don't fear the sweet honey syrup -- put it on the chicken!
The blueberry pancakes are the best pancakes in NYC, making our list of "The Tastes That Make the City: NYC Edition."

items.text: Must, must try the sugar cured bacon. It's some of the best bacon I've ever had
i thought i had my hypothetical last meals all figured out until i had the blueberry pancakes here. unreal.
Sugar Cured Bacon IS YOUR GOD. Worship it accordingly and offer it praise.
Our Readers' Choice WINNER for Best Brunch. We dare you stay away from their dessert cart of chocolate cake and muffins.
Pies and cakes for grown-ups. Try the huevos rancheros.
